### Question: What is the composition of the Gilgit Baltistan Council, and who holds key positions in it? ### Answer: The Gilgit Baltistan Council consists of:
(a) The prime minister of Pakistan;
(b) The governor of Gilgit Baltistan;
(c) Six members nominated by the prime minister of Pakistan from time to time from amongst federal ministers and members of Parliament, with the federal minister for Kashmir Affairs and Gilgit-Baltistan as an ex officio member and minister in charge of the council;
(d) The chief minister of Gilgit-Baltistan;
(e) Six members elected by the Assembly through proportional representation. The prime minister of Pakistan serves as the Chairman, and the governor is the Vice-Chairman of the Council. The Gilgit Baltistan Council virtually wields all authority and power over the affairs of the region.
